Example of file /etc/config/lime for the next scenario:

* protocols OLSR + BMX + BAT-ADV
* OLSR runs on top of the network devices
* BMX and BAT-ADV run in VLAN
* OLSR runs only in specified network devices
* BMX and BAT-ADV run in all network devices



	config lime network
		option primary_interface eth0
		option bmx6_over_batman	'false'
		option main_ipv4_address '192.0.2.0/24'
		option main_ipv6_address '2001:db8::%M5:%M6/64'
		list protocols adhoc
		list protocols lan
		list protocols anygw
		list protocols batadv:%N1
		list protocols bmx6:13
	
	config net ether1
		option linux_name eth1
		option olsr_ip 10.1.1.1/32
		list protocols olsr
		list protocols bmx6:13
		list protocols batadv:%N1
	
	config net wifi2
		option linux_name wlan0-adhoc
		option olsr_ip 10.1.1.2/32 
		list protocols olsr      
		list protocols bmx6:13
		list protocols batadv:%N1
	
	config wifi radio0
		list modes 'adhoc'
		list modes 'ap'
		option channel_2ghz '1'
		option channel_5ghz '48'
		option adhoc_mcast_rate '6000'
		option adhoc_ssid 'libre-mesh'
		option adhoc_bssid 'd2:ca:ff:ee:ba:be'
		option ap_ssid 'LiMe'
	
